THE Standards Organisation of Nigeria, SON, has adopted 10 America Petroleum Institute, API, Standards for the nation’s oil and gas industry. <img class="wp-image-1215843 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/standards-organisation-of-nigeria-squarelogo-1503908538069.png?resize=640%2C640&#038;ssl=1" alt="Standards Organisation of Nigeria" width="640" height="640" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/standards-organisation-of-nigeria-squarelogo-1503908538069.png?w=180&amp;ssl=1 180w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/standards-organisation-of-nigeria-squarelogo-1503908538069.png?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1 107w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/standards-organisation-of-nigeria-squarelogo-1503908538069.png?resize=58%2C58&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/standards-organisation-of-nigeria-squarelogo-1503908538069.png?resize=130%2C130&amp;ssl=1 130w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" />  Director-General/Chief Executive, SON, Osita Aboloma, who disclosed this during a joint Technical Committee meeting on Oil and Gas/Petroleum and Petro Chemicals event in Lagos, said the standards would impact positively on the industry. Aboloma, who was represented by Director, Standards Development, Mrs Chinyere Egwuonwu, revealed that the standards were very relevant to Nigeria. According to him, adopting of international standards as the national standard is not a new development, especially where the standards are elaborated by global leaders such as API who since 1919 have established clout for convening subject matter experts in establishing, maintaining and distributing consensus standards for the oil and gas industry. He said: “The API standards being adopted are recognised not only for their technical specifications but also for their third party accreditation which facilitates acceptance by international bodies and has been a cornerstone in developing standards for the worldwide oil and natural gas industry.” Vanguard ENUGU - FEDERAL Government has commenced training of stakeholders in oil and gas sector on proper metering and measurement in the sector to enhanced national development. March 4, 2019 In "News" The Standards Organisation of Nigeria (SON) and other relevant stakeholders have reviewed standards to revive Nigeria’s ailing paper industry. September 21, 2018 In "Business" Disturbed by incessant building collapse across the country which observers attribute to poor application of cement, stakeholders in the nation’s building/construction industry gathered at a meeting of the Technical Committee on Cement of the Standards Organisation of Nigeria, SON, to review standard for cement (NIS 444 – 1: 2014), with… December 19, 2017 In "Homes & Property"